        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-26T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-26T03:00:00-05:00" n="214" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                    Indonesia/7–2648: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Batavia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Livengood</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d214fn1">Repeated in telegram 344, July 27, 6 p. m., to The
                        Hague.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Batavia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-26T16:00:00+08:00">July 26, 1948—4 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>653. Abbey saw Hatta evening July 25 and communicated gist of Department’s
                        telegram,<note n="2" xml:id="d214fn2">Telegram 347, July 23, <ref target="#pg_288">p. 288</ref>.</note> except last paragraph. Hatta
                    confirmed suspension political negotiations only to last until Dutch Cabinet
                    resumed. He fears that it may be some time before Dutch Cabinet can be formed.
                    He appeared to understand Department’s position fully. With regard to Tuesday’s
                    meeting <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, Hatta said Palar already fully
                    informed and instructed. He reiterated this when queried again later <pb facs="0304" n="290" xml:id="pg_290"/> in conversation, the indication being
                    Palar will not submit any untoward statement in the premise.</p>
                <p>Hatta expressed concern for immediate signing of agreements, appeared more
                    affable and expansive than usual.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Livengood</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
